HEADWORD: Artemis
<hw>Artemis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>the virgin
goddess of the hunt and the moon in Greek mythology; one of the Olympian
deities, daughter of Zeus and Leto and twin sister of Apollo; identified
with the Roman Diana.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Cynthia, Diana.</syn>⟦br⟧
